text:
Petition for BLACKPINK Concert in Armenia

Dear YG Entertainment,

We, the Armenian BLINKs, are writing this petition to express our deep desire to see our favorite group, BLACKPINK, perform in Armenia. BLACKPINK’s music has inspired thousands of Armenian fans, and we strongly believe that Yerevan would be a fantastic location for a concert as part of your upcoming tour.

K-pop has gained immense popularity in Armenia, and BLACKPINK has a growing fanbase here. In previous years, global artists like System of a Down and 50 Cent have successfully performed in Armenia, proving that our country is ready to host world-renowned musicians.

We kindly ask you to consider adding Armenia to BLACKPINK’s 2025 tour schedule. Our country is rich in culture, history, and hospitality, and we are confident that a concert here would be a great success.

There are several suitable venues for a BLACKPINK concert, such as:
	•	Karen Demirchyan Sports and Concert Complex (Hamali) (11,000+ capacity)
	•	Hrazdan Stadium (50,000+ capacity)
	•	Republic Square (large outdoor venue for public events)

We are ready to launch social media campaigns, collect signatures, and support the organization of this event in any way possible. We sincerely hope that you will consider our request and give Armenian BLINKs the chance to experience BLACKPINK live.

Thank you for your time and consideration. We eagerly await your response.

Sincerely,
Armenian BLINKs

text:
BLACKPINK メンバーの行動と性格
ジス (キム・ジス) – 穏やかで面白い人

彼女は穏やかで思いやりのある性格です。
メンバーの世話をする、BLACKPINK の「非公式のお母さん」として見られることが多い
Translate:-BLACKPINK Members' Behavior & Personality
Jisoo (Kim Jisoo) – The Calm and Funny One

She has a calm and caring personality.
Often seen as the "unofficial mom" of BLACKPINK, taking care of the members.
Playful and funny, she loves making jokes and teasing the others.
Very confident and strong-willed, rarely showing fear.
Jennie (Kim Jennie) – The Charismatic & Soft-hearted One

Known for her "cold and chic" image on stage but is actually soft and cute off-stage.
Has a strong leadership vibe and often takes the lead in interviews.
Loves fashion and has a natural, elegant charm.
Can be a little shy at first but is very caring towards her members.
Rosé (Park Chaeyoung) – The Sweet & Emotional One

Very kind and emotional, often expressing deep thoughts.
Loves music and can be seen playing the guitar or singing whenever she gets the chance.
She has a soft and friendly personality, making her easy to talk to.
Sometimes a bit clumsy, which fans find adorable.
Lisa (Lalisa Manoban) – The Energetic & Playful One

The most energetic and playful member, always making others laugh.
Loves dancing and is very confident in her skills.
Very friendly and gets along with everyone, even in different languages.
Loves teasing the members but is also very caring towards them.

author: @MarryTELE
text:
We need a comeback, a comeback of Blackpink, the biggest Kpop group in history, with multiple achievements that show the effort and potential that they have been marking for a long time. Blackpink has the attention of every country without leaving another behind. Latin America has never had the opportunity to show how much we love the Pinks. I'm from Chile and everywhere I go people talk about them. It's no small thing to say that my small and recently installed school already has everyone talking about their return. I'm nervous. For all the news and places that are coming and I would consider coming here so that they can try food and get to know our culture both in dance and in the streets, with all my heart I ask you, no country is like ours and well, it is true, all countries have that touch, some more than others but in truth you will not regret it. Blackpink was my childhood and it was all I wanted was for me not to lose faith. Their music encourages me and their choreography even more. I love everything that has to do with them and I hope with all my heart that they join us on their list. Thank you YG for uniting talented girls in a group that empowers them.

🇰🇷 version:

author: @Hannah-g8e1l
text:
رؤية النبي محمد ﷺ في المنام نعمة عظيمة، وهناك أدعية وأعمال يمكن أن تساعد على تحصيل هذا الشرف بإذن الله. من بين هذه الأدعية:

الدعاء:
"اللهم إني أسألك برحمتك التي وسعت كل شيء، وبنور وجهك الذي أشرقت له السماوات والأرض، أن تريني نبيك محمدًا ﷺ في المنام، وتجعل لقائي به سببًا لزيادة إيماني وحبك وحب نبيك الكريم. اللهم اجعلني من أهل رؤيته في الدنيا والآخرة."

نصائح أخرى:

1. الطهارة والوضوء: النوم على طهارة ومع وضوء.


2. الصلاة على النبي ﷺ: الإكثار من الصلاة على النبي قبل النوم مثل: "اللهم صل وسلم على سيدنا محمد عدد خلقك ورضا نفسك وزنة عرشك ومداد كلماتك".


3. قراءة القرآن: قراءة سورة الإخلاص أو سورة الكوثر بتدبر.


4. الإخلاص في النية: أن يكون لديك شوق صادق لرؤية النبي ﷺ.



اجعل قلبك مليئًا بالحب والاتباع للنبي ﷺ، والله يرزقك رؤية الحبيب في المنام بإذنه.

author: @hongeuchae11wantgramaback
text:
**Dear YG Entertainment,**

I am writing to express my opinions  regarding the recently announced BLACKPINK 2025 World Tour. While I am incredibly excited to see the group perform, there are several issues that need to be addressed to ensure the well-being of the members and the quality of the tour.

**Prioritize Jisoo and Her Music:** It is disappointing to see that Jisoo's solo projects have not been given the attention they deserve. As fans, we have been eagerly waiting for her to release her own music, and it is unfair that she has to juggle this with a grueling tour schedule. Please prioritize her solo projects and allow her the time to focus on her music.

**Avoid Overworking the Members:** The health and well-being of Jennie, Jisoo, Rosé, and Lisa should be your top priority. The members have repeatedly expressed how exhausting their previous tours were, and it is unacceptable to subject them to the same level of stress again. There needs to be ample rest and recovery time between performances to ensure they are not overworked.

**Limit Tour Locations:** A world tour with countless locations is simply too much. Focus on key cities in Asia and possibly a few other countries to minimize travel fatigue. This will help reduce the strain on the members and allow them to give their best performances. It is frustrating to see them being pushed to their limits for the sake of covering more locations.

**Avoid Lip-Syncing:** Fans deserve authentic performances. Lip-syncing not only diminishes the concert experience but also undermines the hard work the members put into their music. Ensure that the performances are genuine and live, allowing fans to fully appreciate the talent and effort of BLACKPINK.

**Demand a Full Album:** We have been eagerly waiting for a long, full album from BLACKPINK. A 12+ song album would truly showcase the versatility and talent of the members. It’s high time we get an extensive collection of their music that we can enjoy for years to come.

**Additional Concerns:** The rigorous schedule of the tour should not compromise the members' health. We have seen the physical and emotional toll that such demanding schedules have taken on them in the past, and it is distressing to think that they might have to go through it again. Give them the time and space they need to rest and recover. Overworking them will only lead to burnout and detract from the quality of their performances.

Thank you for taking the time to read this letter. We believe that by addressing these concerns, you will not only ensure the health and well-being of BLACKPINK but also enhance the overall tour experience for fans. Our love and support for the members are unwavering, and we want to see them thrive without compromising their health.
